  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>γραφή[a] in {D:33.10} differs significantly in meaning from γραφή[b] ({D:33.53}) in that the latter denotes specifically some OT Scripture passage, while γραφή[a] is a more generic reference to any unit of discourse, though in {S:04200402100020} it happens to refer to an OT section.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>For γραφή in the more generic sense, see {D:33.10} and footnote.</Content>
    </Note>
