            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-24 21:37:10" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(pl; ῶν f) the sacred writings of the OT</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>the Scriptures</Gloss>
                <Gloss>the holy writings</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Some translators have mistakenly attempted to use the rendering ‘Bible’ when translating αἱ γραφαί ‘the Scriptures’ in the NT. The reference is to the OT and not to the entire Bible, including both New and Old Testaments. It is also a mistake to translate αἱ γραφαί as ‘God’s writings,’ for this would give the impression that God himself wrote the words.</Comments>
